{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Displace Along Normal"], "type": "title", "extent": [73, 99], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [99, 173], "text": ["Displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given amount."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [173, 288], "text": ["This operator displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given\namount. The displacement is anti-aliased."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [288, 478], "text": ["You will often pipe the output of a pattern operator such as Stripes,\nBoxes, or Rings into the \"amount\" input. You can further control the\namount of displacement by the \"scale\" multiplier."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [478, 846], "text": ["Typically, this operator will be used in a displacement shader, with\nboth outputs piped into the corresponding inputs of the ", {"text": ["Output Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/output"}, " operator.\nAlternatively, it can be appear in a surface shader, in which case the\ndisplaced normal would be normalized and then connected to the ", {"text": ["nN"], "type": "code"}, "\ninput of the ", {"text": ["Lighting Model"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}, " operator."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [846, 1044], "text": ["The input normal (", {"text": ["nN"], "type": "code"}, ") should be normalized if explicitly connected. If\nthe position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ") and normal (", {"text": ["nN"], "type": "code"}, ") inputs are not connected, the global\nvariables by the same names will be used instead."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1044, 1102], "text": ["Normals are automatically recomputed and set for output."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [1102, 1247], "text": ["Note that in the SOP/POP contexts, the shears and object space\ndeformation are not implemented. They exist as parameters for\ncompleteness only."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1252, 1573], "text": ["When doing a displacement in RenderMan, be sure to add an\n    ", {"text": ["RSL Transform"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/rsl_transform", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/rsl_transform"}, " node to P before piping it\n    into your noise VOP. Make this \"current to world\" and change the\n    displace space at object level to be the camera you are rendering\n    through. Otherwise the noise will slide."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "tip", "extent": [1247, 1252]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "tip_group"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1607, 1687], "text": ["Overall displacement amount, including the amount for shears."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Displacement Amount"], "role": "item", "extent": [1585, 1607], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 8, "type": "para", "extent": [1694, 1771], "text": ["A multiplier of the amount in the perpendicular direction."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Scale"], "role": "item", "extent": [1687, 1694], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [1573, 1585], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1780, 1803], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/shade/normalmaps", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/shade/normalmaps"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1803, 1825], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/displace", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/displace"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1825, 1854], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/displacetexture", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/displacetexture"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1854, 1873], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/boxes", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/boxes"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1873, 1895], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cavities", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/cavities"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1895, 1919], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/cellcracks", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/cellcracks"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1919, 1941], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/lighting", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/lighting"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1941, 1962], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/scales", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/scales"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1771, 1780], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Displaces the surface along the surface normal by a given amount."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "displacenml", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/displacenml"}, "title": ["Displace Along Normal"]}